=C2=A0Other times the thing never trades above $80, you sell it a year late=
r for $60, and people have some questions about your valuation.Obviously th=
is more or less never happens with publicly traded stocks=C2=A0or Treasury =
bonds: When a thing has an active public trading market, everyone understan=
ds that you mark the thing to its current trading price, whether or not you=
